Your Honor,

I stand before you today to plead guilty to the charge of shoplifting a dress worth approximately 2000 pounds. I would like to apologize for my actions and express my deep regret for the offense I committed. I understand the seriousness of my actions and take full responsibility for them.

I am 18 years old and this is my first offense. I have never been involved in any criminal activity before and have always strived to abide by the law. However, I found myself in a difficult situation where I desired a dress for prom but lacked the financial means to purchase it. While this does not justify my actions, it does provide some context for why I made such a poor choice.

I would like to assure the court that this incident does not reflect my character or my future aspirations. In fact, my ultimate goal is to become a nurse after finishing high school. I am dedicated to putting this unfortunate incident behind me and working towards a better future. I am committed to making amends for my mistake and proving that I am capable of making positive contributions to society.

I understand the gravity of my offense and the impact it may have had on the victim. I would like to state that I am willing to take any necessary steps to compensate for the harm caused and prevent any further harm in the future. I have already taken steps towards this by expressing my remorse and regret for my actions.

Your Honor, I humbly request that you consider the mitigating factors present in my case. I am pleading guilty, which demonstrates my acceptance of responsibility. I am also a young individual who made a misguided decision due to my desire for a dress I could not afford. Furthermore, I have no prior criminal record, indicating that this offense is an isolated incident.

I assure Your Honor that I have learned a valuable lesson from this experience and I am determined to make better choices moving forward. I respectfully ask for your leniency and the opportunity to prove that I am capable of redeeming myself.

Thank you for your time and consideration.

Sincerely,
Melissa Cox
